{
  "texts": [
    "As before, we need to ensure IR-convergence.",
    "We will therefore work with the following interactions:S int = d 3 xdη a Λ 2 1 π ′ c ∂ i ∂ j π c σ ij + 1 Λ 3 2 ϵ ijk ∂ i π ′ c ∂ j ∂ l π c σ kl,(5.32)where the first term is dimension-6 while the second is dimension-7.",
    "These are the only operators with those mass dimensions and are the leading ones which are IR-finite.",
    "The corresponding EFToI operators are δg 00 δK µν Σ µν and n µ ε µναβ ∇ ν δg 00 δK αγ Σ γ β.",
    "In the CCM scenario the conformal weight of the massive field is the same as that of a massless scalar so the counting of the scale factors is simply 4 -(total number of derivatives)."
  ]
}